<div class="container" style=" color:rgb(10, 7, 2);border-color: darkorange ;text-align: left;" id=ncctopic1>
    <ul>
    The D.A.V NCC company Junior Wing under the control of 1(Tamil Nadu) Battalion NCC , 
    Madras – A Group was started in 1978. The objective of National Cadet Corps is to develop character, comradeship, and capacity for the leadership among youth in India. The motto of NCC is “Unity and Discipline.“ In a nutshell, the values of NCC are as follows: “Sense of patriotic commitment, respect for diversities, commitment to learn and adhere to norms and values, understanding the value of a just and impartial exercise of authority, ability to participate in community development, healthy lifestyle, being sensitive to the needs of the poor “.
     <br><br>
    The National Cadet Corps (NCC) is the youth wing of the Indian Armed Forces. DAV Boys Senior Secondary School, Chennai gives eminence to NCC. Our School Management, Secretary, Director, Principal & ANO motivates the students to be part of NCC from 8th grade onwards.
     <br><br>
     We have regular weekly training in NCC. The Cadets are given basic military training in small arms and drill. 
     <br><br>
    Regular visits by NCC Officers motivate the students to participate in NCC camps being held at various places across the country.
     <br><br>
    This year commencing from April 2022, we had NCC camps held at various places in and around TamilNadu..
</ul>
    
