    The Eighth International Day of Yoga was observed in our school as ' Yogathon under the guidance of 1 (TN) BN NCC on 21 June 2022		
 It commenced with 160 NCC Cadets from 5 different schools and 2 colleges performing     Yogasanas from 6.00 a.m. to 8.00 a.m.
 <br><br>
 <b>Thal Sainik Camp (TSC):</b>
 <br>
DAV Gopalapuram NCC cadets participated in THAL SAINIK CAMP(TSC) selection held at Dhanalakshmi Engineering College from 25th April to 4th May 2022.
 <br>
(i)SGT ADITHYA RAMANATHAN<br>
(ii) SGT SHRAVAN C.M<br>
(iii) L/CPL THAMILMARAN.C. S<br>
(iv) CDT MANUSH<br>
(v) CDT DEEPESH KARTHICK.B<br>
<br>
The above mentioned 5 cadets along with the Associate NCC Officer (ANO) participated and gained more insights about NCC at THAL SAINIK CAMP(TSC).
 <br><br>
The next camp was a 10 day camp held at VIT college, Vellore. Camp was held between May 9th and May 18th 2022. Training in Rifle shooting was given as part of this NCC training. 
 <br><br>
Third & fourth NCC camp were held at SRM college, Kattankulathur from May 3rd week to June 2nd week.
 <br><br>
SGT ADITHYA RAMANATHAN- Achievements in THAL SAINIK CAMP(TSC):<br>
He completed the TSC LAUNCH CAMP which was held at Sai Ram Engineering College, West Tambaram- Chennai
He attended state level firing competition and secured 3rd place in Snap Shooting in TSC IGC Inter Group Competition.
